The winner will play either Russia or Croatia, who meet later on Saturday, in the semi-finals. SAMARA - A thumping 30th-minute Harry Maguire header from a corner gave England a 1-0 lead over Sweden in their 2018 World Cup quarter-final on Saturday. Centre-back Maguire connected with an Ashley Young corner to score his first international goal and reward England for their more adventurous approach in a largely cautious first half. The winners will play either Russia or Croatia, who meet later on Saturday, in the semi-finals. 